The Vice President delivered a speech at the South Court Auditorium, celebrating Passover with Rabbi Brous and other guests. She expressed her gratitude to Rabbi Brous and the Milton Gottesman Jewish Day School for organizing the event. The Vice President also welcomed distinguished guests, including Jacky Rosen and members of Congress. She mentioned that her family, like many others, would be celebrating Passover, and reflected on the importance of the holiday, emphasizing the resilience of the human spirit and the fight for freedom. The Vice President concluded by wishing everyone a happy Passover and introducing the children of IKAR for a final word.